cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CY 

The paper deals with the problem of representing an arbitrary predicate as the inner product predicate on two vectors, which is a problem in cryptography. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves encoding and representing vectors, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The problem of matching vector families is a combinatorial problem, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses lower bounds and upper bounds, which are related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
